g.aria-label: Annual world rainfall, renewable resource, exploitable resource, and actual water withdrawal. The renewable resource is the amount of fresh water that can beharvested sustainably, while the exploitable resource is the amount of fresh waterthat can be harvested sustainably, under economic constraints.Source: AQUASTAT.Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. "AQUASTAT".Accessed February 13, 2020.
